import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_sizes = data['group'].value_counts()
    plt.hist(group_sizes, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Group Sizes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_group_size = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().mean()
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count()
    
    ax = group_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.axhline(avg_group_size, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_group_size:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average group size?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
